#   BRO-001: render the hunk status/header line as a full-width banner

The shared hunk renderer draws a hunk's status/header line (the `{ts, verb,
uri}` metadata row — `dog/HUNK.h`, currently a plain `<date>\t<verb>\t<uri>`
in text mode) without a clear visual band. Make it a proper banner: abbreviated
time + URI on a pale-yellow, full-width, black-text line. This is the shared
renderer used by every projector (log/status/grep/diff/commit/blame), so the
fix lands once and benefits all. Prerequisite for [BLAME-005].

##  Input

### Context
 -  A `hunk` is `{ ron60 ts; ron60 verb; u8cs uri; text/toks }`; the status
    line is the `ts`/`verb`/`uri` row the renderer emits (`HUNKu8sFeedText/
    Color/Html` in `dog/HUNK.c`, consumed by [Bro]).
 -  Today the line has no distinct band — it reads as ordinary text and is
    easy to miss between content bodies.

### Goals
 -  The status/header line displays the *time in abbreviated format*
    (`Fri12`-style, the same formatter `be head`/`log:` already use) *and the
    URI*.
 -  Style: *pale-yellow background, spanning the FULL line width* (not just
    the text), *black text*.

### Constraints
 -  Shared renderer (`dog/HUNK.c` `HUNKu8sFeedColor` for the TTY path; keep
    Text/Html modes coherent) — benefits all projectors, no per-producer code.
 -  Reuse the existing abbreviated-date formatter (don't roll a new one).
 -  Full-width fill must respect the terminal width bro already knows.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  Open: does the banner keep the `verb` (the hunk's third field) alongside
    time + URI, or show only time + URI as stated? Default: keep `verb` (it's
    free data) unless it crowds the line.
 -  Open: Text (non-TTY) and Html modes — match the banner intent (Html =
    pale-yellow row, already close per the `ulog` div) or leave Text plain.

